id: pm-ok47
title: pm package doctor should warn when a schema package registers item types/fields but declares narrow activation.commands (silently non-global)
description: "From pm-halx finding: a package that registers custom item types/fields via registerItemTypes/registerItemFields AND declares narrow manifest activation.commands will not have those types available to built-in commands (pm create/list/validate) because lazy activation only fires for the listed commands. This is a silent footgun. pm package doctor activates the package (so it knows the real registrations) and reads the manifest, so it could detect 'registrations.item_types/item_fields non-empty AND manifest.activation.commands present AND the registered surfaces are global schema contributions' and emit an advisory warning recommending the author drop activation.commands (or document that the type is intentionally command-scoped). Advisory/doctor-only (not health-blocking)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:extensions","area:schema",doctor
